

1
00:00:14.166 --> 00:00:14.716 A:middle
&gt;&gt; Good morning.

2
00:00:15.766 --> 00:00:18.846 A:middle
And welcome to WWDC
session on iAd Workbench.

3
00:00:20.006 --> 00:00:22.726 A:middle
I'm Paresh Rajwat and I'm
here with my colleague,

4
00:00:23.006 --> 00:00:26.616 A:middle
Ravi Chittari, to share with
you how we're evolving the iAd

5
00:00:26.616 --> 00:00:27.626 A:middle
Workbench platform.

6
00:00:28.116 --> 00:00:31.576 A:middle
We have some awesome stuff we
are bringing to you this fall,

7
00:00:32.006 --> 00:00:33.656 A:middle
and I can't wait to
share it with you.

8
00:00:34.666 --> 00:00:37.996 A:middle
But before we go there, knowing
some of you are probably new

9
00:00:37.996 --> 00:00:41.406 A:middle
to advertising, and perhaps
hearing the word iAd Workbench

10
00:00:41.406 --> 00:00:42.236 A:middle
for the first time.

11
00:00:43.046 --> 00:00:45.426 A:middle
Let's start with two
foundational questions.

12
00:00:46.626 --> 00:00:47.576 A:middle
Why advertise?

13
00:00:49.196 --> 00:00:49.956 A:middle
And why iAd?

14
00:00:49.956 --> 00:00:54.136 A:middle
Let's start with the first
question: why advertise.

15
00:00:54.736 --> 00:00:59.806 A:middle
Say you developed this app, you
put a lot of time and energy

16
00:00:59.806 --> 00:01:04.426 A:middle
in it and you put
it on the App Store.

17
00:01:04.616 --> 00:01:05.966 A:middle
Now two things can happen.

18
00:01:06.856 --> 00:01:11.526 A:middle
First, users can find
your app, or second,

19
00:01:12.086 --> 00:01:14.506 A:middle
you can find users for your app.

20
00:01:15.126 --> 00:01:18.276 A:middle
Users will find your app
if they know about you,

21
00:01:19.726 --> 00:01:21.336 A:middle
or your app is featured in one

22
00:01:21.336 --> 00:01:24.726 A:middle
of the categories
in the App Store.

23
00:01:24.926 --> 00:01:27.076 A:middle
But with thousands
of apps coming

24
00:01:27.076 --> 00:01:30.586 A:middle
on the App Store every
day, natural discovery

25
00:01:30.586 --> 00:01:33.206 A:middle
of your app becomes
increasingly difficult

26
00:01:33.936 --> 00:01:35.986 A:middle
and you don't have
much control on it.

27
00:01:36.696 --> 00:01:39.136 A:middle
So what can you do
to take more control

28
00:01:39.496 --> 00:01:43.436 A:middle
of the success of your app?

29
00:01:43.666 --> 00:01:44.776 A:middle
You can advertise.

30
00:01:45.946 --> 00:01:49.036 A:middle
When you advertise, you
can find the right users

31
00:01:49.656 --> 00:01:50.716 A:middle
that will make the difference.

32
00:01:51.736 --> 00:01:56.116 A:middle
And when it comes to advertising
your apps or your products

33
00:01:56.916 --> 00:01:59.786 A:middle
to millions of Apple
costumers around the world,

34
00:02:01.116 --> 00:02:03.376 A:middle
iAd is your best choice.

35
00:02:04.756 --> 00:02:11.316 A:middle
Why? Because iAd is part of
Apple, and we know Apple users,

36
00:02:12.286 --> 00:02:14.036 A:middle
all 800 million of them.

37
00:02:15.146 --> 00:02:18.886 A:middle
We know what apps and other
items content they downloaded

38
00:02:19.606 --> 00:02:22.236 A:middle
and we know how and
when they use it.

39
00:02:22.976 --> 00:02:26.966 A:middle
Last June, we introduced
iAd Workbench.

40
00:02:27.886 --> 00:02:31.066 A:middle
It's self-service mobile
advertising platform

41
00:02:32.046 --> 00:02:36.186 A:middle
that provides you the simplest
way to promote your product

42
00:02:37.046 --> 00:02:38.846 A:middle
to millions of Apple
users around the world.

43
00:02:39.256 --> 00:02:42.496 A:middle
Since we introduced
iAd Workbench,

44
00:02:42.766 --> 00:02:44.906 A:middle
we have successfully
helped developers,

45
00:02:46.076 --> 00:02:50.056 A:middle
many of them advertising for the
very first time, drive millions

46
00:02:50.056 --> 00:02:52.706 A:middle
of visits to their
iTunes product pages.

47
00:02:54.026 --> 00:02:56.906 A:middle
iAd Workbench is
open to everyone.

48
00:02:57.986 --> 00:03:01.506 A:middle
And you can promote
anything using iAd Workbench.

49
00:03:02.516 --> 00:03:03.796 A:middle
You can promote your apps.

50
00:03:04.866 --> 00:03:08.436 A:middle
You can promote your products,
your brands, your service,

51
00:03:08.436 --> 00:03:11.256 A:middle
including your iTunes content,

52
00:03:11.646 --> 00:03:14.656 A:middle
whether it's music,
books or movies.

53
00:03:15.256 --> 00:03:19.756 A:middle
Last June when we
introduced iAd Workbench,

54
00:03:19.976 --> 00:03:22.266 A:middle
we started in the U.S.
as the first market.

55
00:03:22.266 --> 00:03:24.896 A:middle
And then a few months
after that,

56
00:03:25.416 --> 00:03:26.886 A:middle
we expanded internationally.

57
00:03:27.556 --> 00:03:31.136 A:middle
iAd Workbench is now
available in 14 countries

58
00:03:32.046 --> 00:03:33.116 A:middle
and expanding rapidly.

59
00:03:33.686 --> 00:03:37.986 A:middle
Now creating a campaign using
iAd Workbench is very easy.

60
00:03:39.386 --> 00:03:41.536 A:middle
You can create one in
just a few minutes.

61
00:03:42.856 --> 00:03:48.036 A:middle
To demonstrate, why don't I have
Ravi show you how easy it is

62
00:03:48.036 --> 00:03:49.446 A:middle
to advertise using
iAd Workbench.

63
00:03:50.396 --> 00:03:51.256 A:middle
&gt;&gt; Thank you, Paresh.

64
00:03:52.456 --> 00:03:53.256 A:middle
Good morning everyone.

65
00:03:54.066 --> 00:03:56.206 A:middle
I'm Ravi Chittari from
iAd Engineering team.

66
00:03:56.736 --> 00:03:58.566 A:middle
I'm here to demo iAd Workbench.

67
00:03:58.996 --> 00:04:06.256 A:middle
In this demo, you will see how
easy it is to promote an app.

68
00:04:06.506 --> 00:04:10.656 A:middle
During this demo, you will see
several options, but I'm going

69
00:04:10.656 --> 00:04:13.196 A:middle
to focus on a few and
will cover more later.

70
00:04:14.306 --> 00:04:15.786 A:middle
Let's get started.

71
00:04:17.546 --> 00:04:21.666 A:middle
iAd Workbench is accessible
through iadworkbench.apple.com.

72
00:04:22.406 --> 00:04:25.846 A:middle
All you need is an
Apple ID to log in.

73
00:04:26.116 --> 00:04:30.026 A:middle
When you log in, the first page
you go to is the Dashboard.

74
00:04:30.996 --> 00:04:32.926 A:middle
Dashboard is a summary
of all the campaigns,

75
00:04:33.896 --> 00:04:35.266 A:middle
and also it gives basic metrics.

76
00:04:35.896 --> 00:04:38.156 A:middle
To get into the campaign
creation flow,

77
00:04:38.636 --> 00:04:39.916 A:middle
let's click on Create Campaign.

78
00:04:44.836 --> 00:04:47.486 A:middle
The first choice you have is
what do you want to promote?

79
00:04:48.896 --> 00:04:50.316 A:middle
App or a Product?

80
00:04:52.076 --> 00:04:55.096 A:middle
Let's select App.

81
00:04:55.346 --> 00:04:59.256 A:middle
Below are the three apps that
are published to the App Store

82
00:04:59.606 --> 00:05:01.846 A:middle
from my developer account.

83
00:05:01.846 --> 00:05:05.416 A:middle
iAd Workbench automatically gets
all the apps that you published

84
00:05:05.416 --> 00:05:07.786 A:middle
to the App Store and
makes it available here

85
00:05:08.606 --> 00:05:11.666 A:middle
so you can promote
through campaigns.

86
00:05:12.176 --> 00:05:13.716 A:middle
Let me select Klara.

87
00:05:13.716 --> 00:05:19.896 A:middle
For a bid type, my goal
is to drive downloads.

88
00:05:19.986 --> 00:05:22.786 A:middle
I'm going to select
CPC, cost per click.

89
00:05:23.246 --> 00:05:26.506 A:middle
Let me name my campaign.

90
00:05:34.136 --> 00:05:37.966 A:middle
Clicking on Next will take
me to step 2, Targeting.

91
00:05:38.826 --> 00:05:40.936 A:middle
Targeting is all about
finding the right audience

92
00:05:40.936 --> 00:05:41.546 A:middle
for your campaign.

93
00:05:41.546 --> 00:05:44.746 A:middle
We have two options,
Auto and Manual.

94
00:05:45.766 --> 00:05:49.166 A:middle
In case of Auto, iAd finds
the right audience for you.

95
00:05:49.716 --> 00:05:52.786 A:middle
In case of Manual, you get to
set the targeting preferences.

96
00:05:53.226 --> 00:05:55.956 A:middle
Let me set up Auto.

97
00:05:56.176 --> 00:05:57.986 A:middle
Next, country where
your ad is going to run.

98
00:05:58.176 --> 00:06:00.066 A:middle
I'm going to select
United States.

99
00:06:01.466 --> 00:06:05.286 A:middle
Next, Ad. Ad is a combination
of Creative and Destination.

100
00:06:05.876 --> 00:06:08.456 A:middle
I'm going to select
Banner for Creative

101
00:06:09.126 --> 00:06:10.366 A:middle
and Destination: iTunes.

102
00:06:11.676 --> 00:06:15.136 A:middle
iTunes destination refers to
the App Store product page

103
00:06:15.806 --> 00:06:18.796 A:middle
where user can review
the app details

104
00:06:18.796 --> 00:06:22.176 A:middle
and download the app
right from there.

105
00:06:22.306 --> 00:06:23.116 A:middle
Next, flight dates.

106
00:06:24.586 --> 00:06:26.646 A:middle
These are the dates during which
your campaign is going to run.

107
00:06:27.556 --> 00:06:30.446 A:middle
The default started is today
and ended is a month from now.

108
00:06:30.976 --> 00:06:32.806 A:middle
Let's leave it as is.

109
00:06:33.186 --> 00:06:33.826 A:middle
Next, budget.

110
00:06:33.826 --> 00:06:36.166 A:middle
How much money you are willing
to spend on this campaign?

111
00:06:36.166 --> 00:06:38.406 A:middle
Let me enter 2,000 dollars.

112
00:06:40.096 --> 00:06:41.996 A:middle
Daily Spend Goal is
automatically calculated.

113
00:06:43.786 --> 00:06:47.916 A:middle
CPC Bid: how much you are
willing to pay per click,

114
00:06:48.826 --> 00:06:50.506 A:middle
the maximum you're
willing to pay per click.

115
00:06:50.696 --> 00:06:54.546 A:middle
You may enter 50 cents.

116
00:06:54.596 --> 00:06:56.456 A:middle
Let's leave the CPA
Goal optional.

117
00:06:57.646 --> 00:07:01.496 A:middle
Clicking on Calculate will
give us the estimated number

118
00:07:01.496 --> 00:07:04.726 A:middle
of impressions and tabs.

119
00:07:04.726 --> 00:07:08.516 A:middle
If you want to see more
impressions and tabs,

120
00:07:08.636 --> 00:07:11.526 A:middle
you can change the combination
of targeting, budget,

121
00:07:11.526 --> 00:07:17.056 A:middle
and bid, and you'll see more.

122
00:07:17.256 --> 00:07:18.586 A:middle
Next, let's name our line.

123
00:07:19.186 --> 00:07:21.876 A:middle
I've used the term "line"
several times in this page.

124
00:07:22.706 --> 00:07:23.216 A:middle
What is line?

125
00:07:23.926 --> 00:07:27.576 A:middle
A line is a combination of
targeting, budget, and bid.

126
00:07:27.796 --> 00:07:29.626 A:middle
You can have several
lines in a campaign.

127
00:07:30.616 --> 00:07:34.626 A:middle
I'm going to name this
line, My Simple Auto Line.

128
00:07:36.076 --> 00:07:39.756 A:middle
Clicking on Next will take me
to the Targeting Summary page

129
00:07:40.566 --> 00:07:41.856 A:middle
where all the lines are listed.

130
00:07:42.356 --> 00:07:44.436 A:middle
For this campaign, we
have just one line.

131
00:07:45.136 --> 00:07:47.626 A:middle
You can always add more lines by
clicking on Create Line button.

132
00:07:48.836 --> 00:07:54.226 A:middle
Clicking on Next will take us to
step 3, which is Creating an Ad.

133
00:07:55.336 --> 00:07:57.846 A:middle
The first choice we have
is selecting a device

134
00:07:57.846 --> 00:07:58.876 A:middle
where your ad is going to run.

135
00:07:59.606 --> 00:08:02.726 A:middle
Klara is a universal app,
so the system detected that

136
00:08:02.726 --> 00:08:05.136 A:middle
and gave iPhone,
iPad on Universal.

137
00:08:05.626 --> 00:08:06.556 A:middle
Let's select Universal.

138
00:08:07.716 --> 00:08:09.286 A:middle
For language, let's
stick with English.

139
00:08:09.696 --> 00:08:10.916 A:middle
We have more choices
there as well.

140
00:08:12.006 --> 00:08:13.796 A:middle
Then let's define the creative.

141
00:08:14.276 --> 00:08:18.166 A:middle
There are two choices, Using a
Template and From My Desktop.

142
00:08:18.966 --> 00:08:23.966 A:middle
From My Desktop is
upload your own Banner.

143
00:08:25.396 --> 00:08:27.366 A:middle
But for now, let's
select templates.

144
00:08:27.366 --> 00:08:31.276 A:middle
We have built several templates
for you to make it easy.

145
00:08:32.196 --> 00:08:36.666 A:middle
As you can see, there
are different formats

146
00:08:36.666 --> 00:08:37.466 A:middle
for these templates.

147
00:08:38.546 --> 00:08:39.476 A:middle
Let me select marigold.

148
00:08:42.126 --> 00:08:46.106 A:middle
For title, let's give
the name of the app.

149
00:08:47.046 --> 00:08:50.106 A:middle
And for message, few
words about your app.

150
00:08:52.956 --> 00:08:56.776 A:middle
And for Call to Action, you
have several predefined ones

151
00:08:56.946 --> 00:08:58.626 A:middle
or you can always
enter a custom text.

152
00:08:59.366 --> 00:09:00.486 A:middle
I'm going to select
Download Now.

153
00:09:00.776 --> 00:09:06.526 A:middle
And here is the preview of
how your Banner is going

154
00:09:06.526 --> 00:09:07.306 A:middle
to look on the device.

155
00:09:08.556 --> 00:09:10.106 A:middle
You can click on View All Sizes

156
00:09:10.746 --> 00:09:14.126 A:middle
to see how we have prepared
this creative for iPhone, iPad,

157
00:09:14.196 --> 00:09:15.056 A:middle
portrait and landscape.

158
00:09:18.896 --> 00:09:19.956 A:middle
That's how simple it is.

159
00:09:21.386 --> 00:09:23.056 A:middle
Let's select their
destination, iTunes.

160
00:09:23.056 --> 00:09:29.006 A:middle
As you saw, as soon as I
selected the destination,

161
00:09:30.196 --> 00:09:34.886 A:middle
it's pointing to the
Klara iTunes product page.

162
00:09:34.986 --> 00:09:38.056 A:middle
For this ad to go live,
we need to associate this

163
00:09:38.056 --> 00:09:40.316 A:middle
with the line that
we just created.

164
00:09:43.886 --> 00:09:45.056 A:middle
I'm assigning to the line.

165
00:09:46.116 --> 00:09:52.476 A:middle
We give that name, Marigold 1.

166
00:09:52.666 --> 00:09:55.686 A:middle
Clicking on Next will take
us to the Ad Summary page

167
00:09:56.316 --> 00:09:57.436 A:middle
where you will see all the ads

168
00:09:57.476 --> 00:09:58.806 A:middle
that are created
for this campaign.

169
00:10:01.526 --> 00:10:03.926 A:middle
And you can always
create more Ads from here

170
00:10:04.496 --> 00:10:05.566 A:middle
by clicking on Create Ad.

171
00:10:06.546 --> 00:10:09.066 A:middle
Clicking on Next will take us
to the Campaign Summary page

172
00:10:09.066 --> 00:10:12.946 A:middle
where you can review all
the details in one place.

173
00:10:13.136 --> 00:10:13.896 A:middle
Where you're promoting,

174
00:10:14.566 --> 00:10:16.946 A:middle
what you're targeting,
what are your ads.

175
00:10:18.216 --> 00:10:20.856 A:middle
In case you have not
set up the payment yet,

176
00:10:21.806 --> 00:10:24.636 A:middle
which is a credit card,
you can always click here,

177
00:10:24.636 --> 00:10:25.816 A:middle
but let's Submit.

178
00:10:25.816 --> 00:10:32.236 A:middle
When you submit, the
creatives are submitted

179
00:10:32.236 --> 00:10:33.966 A:middle
for iAd's Certification review.

180
00:10:34.886 --> 00:10:36.976 A:middle
Once they are approved,
your campaign goes live.

181
00:10:38.716 --> 00:10:39.746 A:middle
That's how simple it is.

182
00:10:40.926 --> 00:10:42.086 A:middle
Back to you, Paresh.

183
00:10:42.816 --> 00:10:47.686 A:middle
&gt;&gt; So next, let's take a deeper
dive at the tools, options,

184
00:10:47.686 --> 00:10:49.676 A:middle
controls, flexibility you have

185
00:10:50.146 --> 00:10:53.596 A:middle
in making advertising
work using iAd Workbench.

186
00:10:53.976 --> 00:11:02.526 A:middle
We'll look at the choices you
have in choosing your audience,

187
00:11:03.156 --> 00:11:08.326 A:middle
the controls you have in
setting your price, the tools

188
00:11:08.326 --> 00:11:11.446 A:middle
and options you have to create
an ad that will make an impact,

189
00:11:12.406 --> 00:11:15.366 A:middle
and finally, the data
and insights you have

190
00:11:16.136 --> 00:11:18.936 A:middle
to understand your campaign
performance and optimize.

191
00:11:19.666 --> 00:11:21.826 A:middle
Let's start with
choosing your audience.

192
00:11:22.066 --> 00:11:26.596 A:middle
Selecting the right audience
for your app or product is key.

193
00:11:27.916 --> 00:11:31.126 A:middle
With iAd Workbench, we
make it very easy for you

194
00:11:31.406 --> 00:11:32.516 A:middle
to define your audience.

195
00:11:33.846 --> 00:11:37.896 A:middle
At the highest level,
you have two options.

196
00:11:37.896 --> 00:11:39.686 A:middle
Auto and Manual.

197
00:11:40.316 --> 00:11:44.766 A:middle
Auto targeting, which you saw
in the demo is the simplest

198
00:11:44.766 --> 00:11:47.726 A:middle
and probably the most powerful
option we have on iAd Workbench.

199
00:11:48.816 --> 00:11:52.386 A:middle
This is where iAd does all
the heavy lifting for you.

200
00:11:53.626 --> 00:11:56.656 A:middle
If you want control,
you can choose Manual.

201
00:11:58.016 --> 00:12:01.396 A:middle
When you choose Manual,
you'll have several options

202
00:12:02.716 --> 00:12:03.666 A:middle
to define your audience.

203
00:12:04.346 --> 00:12:07.516 A:middle
On the left side, you see
simple targeting options

204
00:12:08.246 --> 00:12:12.256 A:middle
like gender, age,
geo, and device.

205
00:12:13.266 --> 00:12:16.566 A:middle
You can choose, for age, you
can choose specific age groups

206
00:12:16.706 --> 00:12:17.636 A:middle
that you want to target.

207
00:12:18.526 --> 00:12:23.206 A:middle
For geo, you can choose
or specify states and DMAs

208
00:12:23.336 --> 00:12:24.786 A:middle
that you want to
target for your users.

209
00:12:26.156 --> 00:12:29.366 A:middle
On the right side, there are
some very powerful options.

210
00:12:30.836 --> 00:12:35.046 A:middle
Starting to the top, iTunes
Preferences is an option

211
00:12:35.416 --> 00:12:37.486 A:middle
that is exclusive to iAd.

212
00:12:38.826 --> 00:12:41.036 A:middle
This is where the
power of the App Store

213
00:12:41.196 --> 00:12:44.026 A:middle
and the iTunes Store
comes together

214
00:12:44.186 --> 00:12:45.686 A:middle
to help you find
the right audience.

215
00:12:47.176 --> 00:12:51.616 A:middle
When you make a selection here,
you're basically selecting users

216
00:12:52.166 --> 00:12:57.066 A:middle
who have actually downloaded
content in that category.

217
00:12:57.066 --> 00:13:01.406 A:middle
So if you were to promote
a health and fitness app,

218
00:13:01.666 --> 00:13:05.716 A:middle
wouldn't it be great if you
could choose the audience

219
00:13:05.986 --> 00:13:08.406 A:middle
who like to download
health and fitness apps,

220
00:13:09.526 --> 00:13:12.696 A:middle
or who like to download
fitness and workout music.

221
00:13:13.876 --> 00:13:15.856 A:middle
With iAd Workbench,
you can do that.

222
00:13:16.886 --> 00:13:17.776 A:middle
It's very powerful.

223
00:13:19.116 --> 00:13:22.206 A:middle
The next three options
lets you define

224
00:13:22.686 --> 00:13:24.766 A:middle
where your ad wants-where
you want to show your ad,

225
00:13:25.116 --> 00:13:26.206 A:middle
which is App Channels.

